cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of symbol misalignment estimation and optimal decoding in asynchronous physical-layer network coding systems. This is a fundamental problem in information theory and communication systems. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of physical-layer network coding in asynchronous networks, which is a topic of interest in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper proposes a new whitening transformation to whiten the noise of the double baud-rate samples, which is a signal processing technique. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses the root-raised-cosine pulse to carry signals, which is a commonly used pulse shaping technique in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents simulation results to evaluate the performance of various estimation-and-decoding schemes, which involves computational techniques.
